entries.femaleVariant: What kinds of wines do you have?
Throat's feelin' parched. What've you got?
What kinds of wines do you have?
Maybe I didn't drink Champaradise every day, but Chateau Piquette was all the rage back in Arasaka.
We cater to the cream of the corporate elite. I believe our wines would be sliiightly beyond your price range.
By the looks of you, I doubt their names would tell you anything.
We had good wine at Arasaka.
Oh! Uh... p-please forgive me – a misunderstanding, that's all! Would you like to see the wine list?
How long've you run this place?
How long've you been runnin' this place?
Right away, miss. Arasaka clients are our always first priority.
entries.maleVariant: Right away, sir. Arasaka clients are always our first priority.

entries.femaleVariant: Long as I can remember... Grandad opened the original merchant's back in Cambridge, and then father brought it here – to Night City.
